    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-02T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-02T15:00:00-05:00" n="235"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d235">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 600.939/32</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-02T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 2, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your January 28, 5 p.m. The American Government can not assent to the prohibition
                    of the export to Siberia of merchandise owned by Americans. You will so
                    represent to the Foreign Office and say that in the opinion of the American
                    Government any embargo on exports to Siberia, particularly at this time, is
                    inadvisable. <pb facs="0223" n="173" xml:id="pg_173"/> The attitude of this
                    Government towards the Bolsheviki is set forth in the President’s recent address
                    to Congress<note n="1" xml:id="d235fn1">The President’s address to Congress of
                        Jan. 8 stated war aims and attitude toward Russia.</note> and in
                    Department’s telegrams of January 16, 4 p.m.,<note n="2" xml:id="d235fn2">
                        <ref target="frus1918Russiav02#pg_28">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p.
                            28</ref>, footnote 2.</note> and January 21, 7 p.m.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d235fn3">
                        <ref target="frus1918Russiav02#pg_31">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 31</ref>, footnote 1.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
